x4freetext: Calibration
method used for data conversion.
ILL High Flux Reactor.
Cross section and ternary fission measurements
made at the end of the 87 m curved neutron guide.
Thermal flux of 6.E8 neutrons per cm2 per sec.
Mass and energy measurements made at neutron beam IH1
collimated to 1 cm diameter. Thermal flux of 5.E9
neutrons per cm per sec at target position.
High energy neutron contamination 1.0E-4 %
for cross section and ternary fission  measurements,
2.0E-3 % for mass and energy  measurements.
-NP-F4, containing the following isotopic composition,
in atoms per cent.
Np-237 greater than 99.99,
Np-235 less than 0.0005, Np-236 less than 0.0005,
Np-238 less than 0.003,  Np-239 less than 0.003.
-For cross section and ternary fission measurements
a 382 micro-g Np-237 per cm2 layer was evaporated
onto a mylar backing. For calibration a similar
layer of 10 micro-g U-235 per cm2 was used.
-For mass and energy measurements a 111 micro-g
Np-237 per cm2 layer and a 129 micro-g U-235 per cm2
layer, evaporated onto 30 micro-g per cm2 polyimide
foil were used.
Defined by spectroscopic analysis the amounts of
eventual impurities (in ppm): U-238 - 10, Pu-239 <1,
Cm-244 < 1, U-235 < 1. Via alpha-spectroscopy:
Data taken from reference.
A.P.T.
BIB information and COMMON were added.
Upper-low case correction. Dates were corrected for
4-digits year.SUBENT .011-.014 were added.   M.M.
Counting statistics, detector efficiencies.
